  "remarks": "The Al-Aqsa Foundation was originally founded as Al-Aqsa E.V. in Germany in 1991. The entity claims to be a not-for-profit organisation that collects donations for humanitarian projects in the Palestinian territories, but has links to Hamas.; Listing: The Minister for Foreign Affairs listed this entity on 16 June 2003 under section 15(1) of the Charter of the United Nations Act 1945 (CotUNA), pursuant to Australia's obligations under UNSC resolution 1373 (2001). The Minister declared on 07 November 2019, pursuant to section 15A(2) of COTUNA, that this listing would continue to have effect. Relisted on 13/09/2025 - Charter of the United Nations (Listed Persons and Entities) Amendment (No.2) Instrument 2025.",
